article.description: San Diego State 76, UC San Diego 51
article.headline: San Diego State 76, UC San Diego 51
article.linkText: San Diego State 76, UC San Diego 51
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Wesley Stokes scored 18 points and Chris Manker added a career-high 12 to lead San Diego State to a 76-51 win over UC San Diego on Saturday night. San Diego State jumped out to a 16-2 lead in the first 4 1-2 minutes of the game after Brandon Heath and Stokes hit back-to-back 3-pointers. The Aztecs (5-2) shot 58.6 percent from the floor in the first half on the way to a 45-28 halftime lead. Matthew Sweany scored 12 points to lead UC San Diego (1-3), an NCAA Division II school. Heath, Chris Walton and Aerick Sanders scored 12 points apiece for the Aztecs, who held a 46-25 rebounding edge. Walton had a game-high 10 rebounds. San Diego State, which beat UC San Diego 87-57 last season, has won all six games against the Tritons by an average margin of 29 points per game.
